            reviewDate: 'December 8, 2019',
            semester: 'fall 2019',
            review: "This is an awesome class. I'm in the CS specialization, and I took it as an elective. I'm not that interested in AI, but I took it because all the projects and homework are released early and are auto-graded. Also, there are no exams. I like to work ahead, so I finished everything in seven weeks. Since it was my last class in OMSCS, that gave me nine weeks to relax before graduation. It's the perfect final class.\nDr. Summet is super responsive and highly involved in the course. I wish all OMSCS instructors were as involved. The TAs were all knowledgeable, nice, and involved as well. Dr. Summet led weekly office hours, which were all recorded, and the TAs were often involved in those as well.\nWe did five projects and six homework problem sets. There were no group projects, and the textbook wasn't necessary. We used Python 2.7 and Bonnie auto-graders, but next semester they're upgrading everything to use Python 3 and Gradescope.\nEverything about this course is extremely well managed. I highly recommend it if you're a self-starter that likes challenging coding projects.",
